            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "`BufLeave` is also emitted. Simpler repo:\n\n```lua\nlocal num_buf_leave = 0\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"BufLeave\", {\n  callback = function() num_buf_leave = num_buf_leave + 1 end,\n})\n\nlocal num_buf_enter = 0\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"BufEnter\", {\n  callback = function() num_buf_enter = num_buf_enter + 1 end,\n})\n\n-- Create a new, unfocused window.\nlocal new_win = vim.api.nvim_open_win(0, false, {\n  split = \"left\",\n  win = 0,\n})\n\nlocal new_buf = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\n\n-- Set the buffer in the unfocused window.\nvim.api.nvim_win_set_buf(new_win, new_buf)\n\n-- The current window never changed, so neither event should've been fired.\nassert(num_buf_leave == 0)\nassert(num_buf_enter == 0)\n```",
